The paper deals with image representation learning using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) without human annotation. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. The paper also introduces a new network architecture called the context-free network (CFN), which is a siamese-ennead CNN, and proposes a novel method for learning visual representations. This could potentially fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on transfer learning benchmarks, which could fall under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) category.
